[[File:Universe expansion2.png|241px|thumb|According to the Big Bang model, the [[Universe]] expanded from an extremely dense and hot state and continues to expand today. A common analogy explains that [[space]] itself is expanding, carrying [[galaxy|galaxies]] with it, like spots on an inflating balloon. The graphic scheme above is an artist's concept illustrating the expansion of a portion of a flat universe.]]
{{Cosmology|cTopic=Key topics}}
The '''Big Bang''' theory is the prevailing [[physical cosmology|cosmological]] model that describes the early development of the Universe.<ref>
